      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Output comparison was performed at the required level. Standard metrics applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI relevance at level 2 requires that the simulated quantities of interest map directly to the clinical endpoint under assessment. The relative hemolysis index (RH) must be demonstrably linked to the plasma free hemoglobin outcome used in bench testing.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed from the power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks. NIH is directly converted to the relative hemolysis index RH used in the bench test protocol. The mapping is validated against published FDA benchmark data and the correlation coefficient between simulated and measured NIH across five operating points is r² = 0.94."
    },
